    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><strong>Dreyfus</strong> is a large grey hound with pale, almost silver eyes. He never leaves High King Harald's side. He does not blink. He watches mouths more than hands. He does not eat&mdash;his bowl by the hearth has been full for days. He does not sleep.</p><p>Dreyfus is not a dog. He is a <em>shape-walker</em>&mdash;a fragment of Grafvitnir's will given form. Bound by guest-right within Hrafnborg, he cannot directly harm those under the King's protection, but he listens to every word, every plan, every name spoken in the King's chambers, and relays it through Wyrd-channels to Grafvitnir's agents in the field.</p><p>In Act 1, Dreyfus is an observer&mdash;patient, silent, and terrifyingly clever. His true combat form is not revealed until Act 2.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
